{"type":"item.completed","item":{"id":"item_46","type":"agent_message","text":"# Review: SUGGESTIONS\n\n## Required Changes\n1. **Durable start/stage boundaries**: The start boundary and stage-commit boundary do not meet the spec’s atomicity requirements.\n   - Current: [`engine.rs`](/root/new-ralph-burning/ralph-burning-rewrite/src/contexts/workflow_composition/engine.rs#L173) appends `run_started` before writing `run.json`, and [`engine.rs`](/root/new-ralph-burning/ralph-burning-rewrite/src/contexts/workflow_composition/engine.rs#L326) writes the payload/artifact pair before the `stage_completed` journal entry and next snapshot update. If journal or snapshot persistence fails at [`engine.rs`](/root/new-ralph-burning/ralph-burning-rewrite/src/contexts/workflow_composition/engine.rs#L347) or [`engine.rs`](/root/new-ralph-burning/ralph-burning-rewrite/src/contexts/workflow_composition/engine.rs#L365), the code returns `StageCommitFailed` without rollback or `run_failed`, so partial durable history can remain visible while `run.json` is left in the prior `running` state.\n   - Expected: `run start` should persist the running snapshot before `run_started`/`stage_entered`, and a successful stage should only become visible once payload, artifact, `stage_completed`, and the next-stage snapshot are all durably committed. On journal/snapshot failure, the stage must remain uncommitted with no visible payload/artifact pair or `stage_completed`, and the run must persist failed state at the current durable boundary.\n   - Reference: Loop 6 acceptance criteria “On successful start…”, “A stage is successful only after…”, and “Failure invariants are explicit…”\n\n2. **Final review routing**: `final_review` is mapped to the wrong role, so the engine resolves the wrong backend/model for that stage.\n   - Current: [`domain.rs`](/root/new-ralph-burning/ralph-burning-rewrite/src/shared/domain.rs#L237) routes `StageId::FinalReview` to `Reviewer`, and [`workflow_engine_test.rs`](/root/new-ralph-burning/ralph-burning-rewrite/tests/unit/workflow_engine_test.rs#L82) asserts that behavior.\n   - Expected: `completion_panel` and `final_review` must both map to `CompletionJudge`, per the spec’s centralized stage-to-role mapping.\n   - Reference: Loop 6 acceptance criterion “Stage-to-role mapping is deterministic and centralized…”\n\n## Recommended Improvements\n1. Add explicit failing-port tests for journal-append and snapshot-write errors, plus the CLI/conformance case for mid-stage failure without partial durable-history exposure. I could not rerun `cargo test` or `cargo clippy` here because `cargo` is not available on `PATH`."}}
